            {
                id = "corners", speaker = "Maerin",
                text = "*(The glare falters — not softening, but *seen*, which is harder to defend against.)* ...Flattened. *(quietly, the fury banking into something rawer.)* Yes. That's the word. That's the *exact* word. *(she looks at her own fading hands.)* Everyone keeps trying to *comfort* me — *you'll be remembered, you'll be honored, your sacrifice* — and all of it is *sandpaper.* Remembered *smooth.* Honored *featureless.* A *sacrifice* doesn't get to have been *unfair to the fishmonger's son for no reason* — but I *was*, and I'd *do it again*, and that pettiness is *more* me than any noble fading. *(she meets your eyes, fierce and grateful and furious at being grateful.)* You said *corners.* Nobody's offered to keep the *corners.* They want the *martyr*; you're offering to carry the *brat.* *(a flickering, real laugh.)* Gods, that's the kindest thing anyone's said to me since I died. Keep the corners, Returned. All of them. The cruelty and the comedy and the boat. If I have to be carried, let me be carried *sharp.* I'd rather cut the hand that holds me than melt in it.",
