            {
                id = "father", speaker = "Maerin",
                text = "*(The fury gentles — this, she'll allow, this one thing.)* My father. *(her fading face softens, just at the edges.)* Aldric. He's a *terrible* merchant, Returned — *terrible* — because he can't lie and he can't haggle and he *cries at weddings he wasn't invited to.* *(a wet, flickering laugh.)* The boat — we were on the river, and I did an *imitation* of the harbormaster, this pompous old walrus, and my father laughed so hard he went *backward off the gunwale*, fully clothed, into the *Chionthar*, and came up *still laughing*, and the harbormaster was *right there* and saw the *whole thing.* *(she wipes a fading eye.)* That's the man. Not *the grieving father.* The man who falls off boats laughing at his daughter's cruelty to walruses. *(her voice drops, fierce again.)* And he's about to lose *that* — lose the *laughing* — and become *the man whose daughter the Wall took*, and it'll *sand him smooth* too, grief does that to the living and the dead *both.* *(she grips your gaze.)* If you do *one* thing with me, Returned: make sure my father gets to *laugh* again before they finish turning us both into a tragedy. He fell off a *boat* for me. The least the world owes him back is one more laugh.",
